# Chronic Kidney Disease (CKD) Guidelines
Chronic kidney disease is defined as abnormalities of kidney structure or function lasting more than 3 months.

## Lifestyle
- Control blood pressure and diabetes
- Avoid nephrotoxic drugs (e.g., NSAIDs)

## Medications
- First-line for hypertension in CKD: ACE inhibitors or ARBs
- Sodium-glucose cotransporter-2 inhibitors (SGLT2i) are recommended in diabetic CKD
